flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn what ingress did into durable, run-scoped ingest truth"]
    G2["Make ingest results committed and reconstructable rather than merely observed"]
    G3["Close ingestion through evidence rather than through an impression that runtime activity probably happened"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not that some requests hit ingress"]
    E2["Active ingestion counters are non-zero, or an explicit empty-run waiver exists"]
    E3["This path only begins once ingress has already been live enough to generate meaningful ingest basis"]
    E4["It is downstream of boundary access"]
    E5["It is downstream of admission and disposition"]
    E6["It is downstream of authoritative bus publication"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Run-scoped ingress activity"]
    R2["Managed ingest-commit lane reads authoritative ingress evidence surfaces"]
    R3["Receipt, quarantine, and offset-proof artifacts are built"]
    R4["Ingest-commit verdict is computed and committed"]
    R5["Durable ingest truth for this run"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["receipt_summary.json"]
    C2["quarantine_summary.json"]
    C3["kafka_offsets_snapshot.json"]
    C4["Rollup and execution artifacts that declare whether the ingest-commit lane passed or failed"]
    C5["The offset-proof mode itself is part of the carried truth because proof basis depends on the ingress edge mode"]
    C6["Current API Gateway -> Lambda -> DynamoDB ingress posture uses admission-index proxy proof mode"]
    C7["A direct Kafka ingress edge would use broker topic and partition offsets"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats ingest closure as evidence closure, not just runtime behavior"]
    L2["The system is not satisfied with admissions happened in DynamoDB or messages probably made it to the bus"]
    L3["It requires a bounded artifact set that later phases can read as ingest truth"]
    L4["That is why ingest closure has its own phase and its own blockers"]
    L5["It is not swallowed by streaming activity or RTDL"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["Concrete ingest evidence artifacts live under the run evidence root"]
    S2["evidence/runs/{platform_run_id}/ingest/receipt_summary.json"]
    S3["evidence/runs/{platform_run_id}/ingest/quarantine_summary.json"]
    S4["evidence/runs/{platform_run_id}/ingest/kafka_offsets_snapshot.json"]
    S5["The path reads live ingress basis from the current ingress edge posture"]
    S6["It publishes durable truth into these pinned ingest evidence surfaces rather than leaving it trapped in live runtime stores"]
    S7["The proof rule is concretely seated: current ingress posture uses admission-index proxy mode, while direct Kafka ingress would use broker offset mode"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform explicitly rejected weaker alternatives"]
    Y2["Claiming ingest-commit pass from DynamoDB admissions alone was rejected"]
    Y3["Running the lane locally from the operator shell was rejected"]
    Y4["Forcing broker topic and partition offsets when the current ingress edge does not materially emit them was rejected"]
    Y5["The chosen design kept fail-closed posture but made offset proof mode-aware"]
    Y6["If direct broker offsets are available, use them"]
    Y7["If not, and the edge is API Gateway -> Lambda -> DynamoDB, derive explicit and deterministic admission-index proxy snapshot instead"]
    Y8["The design keeps the truth boundary, adapts proof mode to the actual wired edge, and never silently fabricates broker offsets"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The run-process contract defines the closure rule for ingest commit"]
    X2["Summaries committed"]
    X3["Mode-aware offset proof committed"]
    X4["Dedupe and anomaly checks passing"]
    X5["The handles registry pins the ingress-edge-dependent proof rule"]
    X6["The path is not free to invent its own evidence semantics"]
    X7["Later replay-basis contract depends on this path"]
    X8["Learning-input closure says replay basis must be pinned as origin-offset ranges and defines admission-index proxy mode versus broker-offset mode"]
    X9["So this path is upstream of later replayable learning truth, not just local bookkeeping"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately accepts less pure proof mode in exchange for keeping the current ingress edge and preserving fail-closed semantics"]
    T2["In the current API Gateway -> Lambda -> DynamoDB posture, the ingress edge persists admissions in DynamoDB but does not emit broker topic and partition offsets into stored idempotency rows"]
    T3["The design did not weaken the path into admissions alone are enough"]
    T4["Instead, it kept explicit offset proof but allowed deterministic proxy mode for this edge"]
    T5["That is the real design trade-off: preserve closure discipline while admitting the current edge's evidence limitations honestly"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform still has ingress edge, admission logic, and bus publication"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to what ingest actually committed for this run"]
    N3["It also loses clean answers to what was admitted versus quarantined, what replay basis later lanes should trust, and whether dedupe and anomaly checks actually passed"]
    N4["It becomes unclear whether ingest closure is grounded in durable artifacts or only inferred from live stores"]
    N5["That weakens A immediately because the ingress part of the system stops looking governed and starts looking observational"]
    N6["The docs make this visible by treating missing receipt surfaces and dedupe drift as explicit blockers, not as later debugging concerns"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Admit summary committed"]
    O2["Quarantine summary committed"]
    O3["Offset-proof snapshot committed in the correct evidence mode"]
    O4["Dedupe and anomaly verdict passes"]
    O5["Owned outcome: committed ingest evidence set for this run"]
    O6["This is specifically the point where ingress behavior has been turned into durable ingest truth"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for turning ingress activity into committed ingest truth"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>the path is deliberately evidence-driven, managed, and fail-closed rather than best effort"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the path is concretely seated in explicit ingest evidence artifacts and a pinned edge-dependent proof rule"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>the meaning of offset proof is governed by the run-process and the handles registry, and later feeds replay-basis semantics for learning input"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the current ingress posture cannot honestly supply broker offsets, so the system uses explicit proxy mode rather than pretending otherwise"]
    A6["Closure signal:<br/>the design enforces the truth boundary rather than treating it as decorative; when offset evidence is not materially available, the path fails closed and corrects the proof mode honestly instead of weakening closure into vagueness"]
    A7["A-level meaning:<br/>ingest behavior becomes durable, mode-aware, replay-relevant evidence rather than a guess assembled later from live stores"]
  end

